values:
I am so sick of the whole school experience. I am ready for the summer to come, more than anyone could realize. 
I am annoyed by people because I just do not get them. How can one say that he/she cares about another, but when a problem arises that "caring" person can not even look at the other.
I am hurting, and no one seems to realize this because they are so wrapped up in their lives, which im ok with, or they just think that I am so wrong that I do not even deserve the help, which im not ok with.

Well, my weekend has not been the suckfest I expected. My mom and I had our big fight before we left for Biloxi, so she perked up. The casino was really packed, and the food was not up to its normal standards, but it was still ok. The room was great, but the beds lacked...everything! They hurt really bad and felt like the floor. But, the bathroom had a jacuzzi tub and you could watch tv in it, so i did after I went to the amazing workout room. I went there a couple of times and made the mistake of watching a hunting show on the treadmill, so my legs hurt pretty bad. My mom and I talked the whole way down there and back. Somehow, it was a great, deep conversation that I wished had never stopped. My aunt met us in Biloxi and stayed te night with us. It was great. We all decided it was our escape from men weekend, which I welcomed. I love when all have our girl talks, which we need to do soon! Maybe next Friday can be girls' night, we will see.
In academic news, Dr. Clay let me change my paper topic, so it will now be on Diabetes. I can explain why later, but i don't feel like typing it right now. My paper for government will be a breeze. I found a website about the government structure of the Wizarding World, from Harry Potter. It gives me a perfect outline for the paper. Now, I have to start working on all of this crapload, so I will be free this weekend to go hunting. Yes my friends, it reopens this weekend for another week and a half!! 
Hope some of you had fun planting trees...hehe, I'm too sick to go!
ill c everyone 2morrow. that 2005 thingy is on my comments page, i still cant do lj cuts. dont laugh.i need to fold laundry, byes!

ugh. i am so freakin tired. i have barely slept since my aunt died because i have been waking up about every 30 min, so the time i do sleep is precious. i decided to go huntin friday mornin so that meant i was up at five. but, me, jamie, n mark went to work at the pizzeria yesterday afternoon. we clocked on at three and deliveries were practically nonexistent so they had to clock off really early (bout 9 i think). i tried to leave then, but ppl kept streaming through the door like rain through a hole in the ceiling, and i forgot my umbrella. i did not even sit down until i finally left at 2 in the mornin. by the time i went to bed it was 3:30. i went huntin all day today, so i was up at 6 this mornin (i slept in). after fighting with dogs, and chasin deer all day im beat.im goin to bed asap. nite

so far, all of my family has done really well dealing with our loss. its hard to tell anyone why this is such a big deal because its a long story, thats very confusing to ppl that do not know my history with my family, which is something i am not willing to discuss. period. im sorry, i mean im really close to u guys, but not that close yet. but i think all of you guys are bright spots for me. when we start talking about the funeral arrangements and such i think of you, and i cheer up just a little. at this point, its hard to let go. the funeral will not be until thursday at 11, so maybe that will bring some closure. i can not believe that for the rest of my life, i will never get a phone call from my aunt again. i just wish this was an extremely bad dream that i will wake up from. but, for her sake, i am glad that she has passed so i can not be selfish and wish this was not true.
 i am very hopeful that next year will be better. and, this experience has brought me a lot closer to my faith which i have strayed from for too many years. im glad u guys have had a great christmas break, so far, and hope the best for you.

hi again from the deep depths of hell.
it is so strange how life happens. my aunt's favorite day has always been christmas. i dont understand how such a great god could take her away two days before christmas. i feel kinda selfish right now, because i am mourning her, which i know is wrong because she is better off away from her pain that her life has become in the last few years. somehow, she has always looked past herself and taken care of everyone else. it just does not feel like christmas. there is no reason to cry when you open presents on christmas morning. this just isnt fair. all the packages were addressed from her and my uncle because she was alive, and she thought she would keep living for a long time. i have really never dealt with this kinda pain before, because the last relative i lost was when i was in 3rd grade, which means i had no idea what was really happening. now, i am old enough to understand i will not see aunt gloria again, and it hurts so bad. i went from being on top of the world and completely ecstatic, to feeling aboslutely devestated with one sentencein a phone call. at least my dad and everyone have dealt with this before, two of my uncles passed away years ago, and they had to deal with that loss. luckily, i have had a very comfortable life. i guess we are going to the funeral home tomorrow to pick everything out, and my uncle and i are going to go through the boxes of pictures he has to find some for the service.i think im gonna give my aunt her christmas present anyway. i just wish that i could get to the point there are no more tears to be shead.

please keep my family in your prayers. we are having a really hard time. my aunt died this morning.

ashley- im glad everything went ok.

 the party was a lot of fun but i have to make some phone calls so i dont have the time to write bout it. c yall l8r

i know i should be getting ready to graduate and go off to college to begin my life my life, but im not ready. i think about everything i have to do now and realize i need to do it now, but im just not motivated at all. i want to just sail around the caribbean and say "screw you" to everyone and everything. no worries, no school, no shoes just relaxation and freedom from everything. i close my eyes and see the warm water brushing the side of my boat that is anchored on a gorgeous island on my right filled trees. i just want to escape. at this point, even medical school feels like it will be a prison that will trap me in debt and work.i shouldnt have to worry about the cost because my mom can afford to send me to whatever school i want. 
 i know my family is relying on me to make a difference in the world, and i want to do it, but i just feel like everything i do should be better. i always thought i was a great student, but i dont have any noominations for anything because i didnt stay at Niceville where i could have succeeded, and at least graduate with high honors. im just one of the crowd, not really a shining star like i want to be, and it bugs me.
 probably the other thing that bothers me is being single. it was ok for a while, but now its getting to my birthday and prom will be here soon. i really want a date for my birthday, or at least some one to take me to prom. ive had some boyfriends and various other types of friends, but i have always been single at every dance and for my senior prom i just feel its unacceptable. i really really really want a date, not one of those "oh i feel so bad for u" ones, but an actual date.
 theres always more to cover about my emotional problems, but dont like to let my personal life out much. sry,or maybe u guys r lucky.

ah, the joys of quiet. yes, boys and girls, my mother is gone!!!!!!!!!! i have already done cartwheels and ran around the house. not really, just on the inside. she always seems to be completely nice and enjoyable before she leaves,like i should actually miss her. but, this time she went against the grain. we have faught all weekend about everything. but, thats all behind me. 
this morning (and yesterday morning) the stupid, wretched mexicans were nailing shingles on a house that is being built at 7 flipping 30! i thought about shooting them with my BB gun until they fell off the roof, but my mom said that would be some kinda misdemeanor. better luck 2morrow morning. maybe ill just call border patrol. hhmmm. ill need to think about that.
im pretty well done with hw. ive even done ALL my research for my economics paper. now i have to write it. yuck. i hate papers like that, the ones that just loom over ur head like a mosquito until the end of the semester when they bite at awkward times.
im gonna go take a shower b4 i go shopping with my dad. tata!

OMFG!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! i love the mullet. terri clark was amazing. she sounded just like she does on her cd, and she sang for an hour and a half. she was even better than when she came to pcola with toby keith. AND moo moo came up to the show. my sister called and found me n my dad and had bella in a stroller with her. me n her danced to a ton of songs; she loved it. we are gonna buy her a baby cowboy hat we found. im tryin to talk my dad into gettin me one that is pink. we'll c. the best thing about my sis, is she kws her alcohol. yes, i did inherit this talent. she brought in crown royal reserve to mix with her coke. yum. her boyfriend bought foster's, so  i got to drink that too. the only thing i hate the mullet is all the ppl we know. me n my dad couldnt walk ten feet, truely, without seeing someone we knew. this was actually a good record for us. its usually worse. it was cool seeing a bunch of my old friends again. some of them want me to ride some of the thingys with them 2morrow. well i need to go to bed, im  not focusing real good. mark- u shoulda called me back. maybe another time.

hey everyone.
i wish i could say that i have had a wonderful weekend full of excitement and fun since ive had no homework. but of course not. my life does not work to my advantage. so far, i have been sick all weekend and have had to endure many grueling hours of what things will be like after i die. 
friday. we had a good talk on the deck about something, but at this point snot is clogging up my brain so i cannot remember what was said. i got home, my mom walked in the door right after me and proceeded to tell me my list of crap to do for the weekend. then, she fell asleep, which sucked because she snores louder than niagra falls and jeopardy was on, and i couldnt change the channel or shed wake up and cuss me out until i turned back to that wretched show. so i called my sister. she came over, which sucked because i had such a fever i did not even want to play with moo moo. yeah, it was that bad. so i tried not to complain, and hoped that i would get over it. well, my mom came up with the bright idea of going out to dinner with the WHOLE FAMILY!!! did u know, i cant kill yourself with the butterknives at Ali Baba's in fwb?! i found out after sitting there for like 1.5 hours with all of the freaks that some consider my relatives. my mom was a pig the whole way back from fwb and tried to get pissed at me for not doing anything around the house for weeks which is complete bs. well, we got home, my sister left with her screaming kid, and i got online when my aunt from louisiana imed me and asked if they could come over. yuck. her and my uncle bothering me why im sick, and my mom in a crappy mood. just what i need.
saturday.took the sat. i could barely see the paper becuase my eyes were watering so bad and i sniffled the whole time. that was the worst morning. but i barely realized how long it took because i was so out of it. got home, my dad was here and had already got into a fight with my mom before i had got home. that sucked. my mom thought it was funny, and my got madder, so my mom laughed more, and it went on. so i left to go run some errands for my mom. the phone call with ali helped. i was able to at least not flip out because at that point i was pissed. got back home and my aunt and uncle walked in the door not too long after i had popped more pills and layed down for a nap. my aunt wanted to go shopping, so my mom begged me to go cuz she hates shopping and gets annoyed wit my aunt. i hate shopping neways, it was worse sick. but i got a bunch of stuff, im talkin a whole bunch!but i still didnt get a freakin jean jacket. grrr. so we got back and went to eat with my dad, which was even worse than when i got home earlier. but the food was good. i went to bed early again. 
today. even sicker. my brother and dad was here today. mom and aunt left to go shopping, but i couldnt be bribed with 50 bucks to leave the air conditioning today. i hate fevers especially when there is an 18 month old running around tearing stuff up who is also sick. its just me n my uncle for now, and we're competing for who gets the tv. but of course, nothing is on. ok, im signing off. time for more tylenol to get my fever down. ttyl!

im finally updating. this is gonna b one of those emo things, that im sure u dont wanna read, i just wanna vent.
i am so sick of my life. it seems like all i do anymore is go to school, come home, do homework, eat, do more homework, go to bed, get up, go to school, and repeat. when i do ge away from the cycle, i get bitched at by my mom because somehow, i had fun and left my responsibilites behind, oh f$#%ing darn. i am so sick of her already, and she has only been home a couple of days. i liked her better before she left because she was nice since she felt guilty about going off and leaving me at home, she does it everytime. if my brother wasnt her in niceville, i doubt she woulda come home, though
my dad doesnt help. all he cares about is how to get my mom back. he is obsessed with her and bella. he could care less from there, you have no idea.
everything just sux anymore. nothing seems to workout, no matter what i try. i keep thinkin that i am on top of my work, and then i get a whole bunch piled on top of me. i just dont know where else to begin explaining. i am sorry everyone, there is a lot more i dont want ya'll to know. as long as i can keep everything else to myself, then i would prefer to keep it that way. i am so bad about keeping this barrier between the world and me, i dont think i have ever let anyone inside that wall. im not trying to be mean or dont trust u guys or something, i am just so bad about keeping things in until it is critical to let it out of my system.i guess im too laid back to let things bother me, instead they just sit in the back of my head and stew. i know im not making any sense, but thats ok, this has really helped. c everyone lateron!

I am really confused right now. i want to be excited and hopeful, but i have a tough time trusting guys. i guess i know some of the ways i ve been in the past, and i am scared of meeting a guy that does those types of things. i dont want a guy that goes out with me so he can get closer to a friend of mine, break up with me because i am too clingy, or, my least favorite move that ive executed, go out with someone becuz u know they like u, and u have to be nice. i am sucha freakin heart-breakin man-eater. i feel horrible about all of these things, and more, but i still dont want someone like that to date me. i am so scared of gettin my heart broke. i just dont feel attractive. its not a self-confidence thing, i think it is more a truth. im gonna wait and see what happens. but i dont wanna wait forever. this year is only so long. i wish hed either just ask me on a date or stop flirting! ggrrr. i am sick of this crap. i like bein blunt, and to the point. i dont wanna waste my time with something that will never develop. at least it is a lot of fun for a little while.

well, i came back from an amazingly good weekend to elections, fightin, gas asses, and tons of stress through the horrendous form of PAPERS. 
of course i was late to skool today also, becuz of the damn gas thing. i was surrounded by assholes that took 45 min at the pumps, and it was only 2 cars!
im not even goin to get into the fight, it would hurt everyone's feelings if i said what i feel. 
not only was there fightin at skool, but when i got home i got into it wit my mom. she was first mad becuz i ate lunch wit my sister and moo moo w/out her. and now she just got mad at me again. i didnt let her talk to my cousin, which woulda had no purpose. also, she hates me goin to see my grandaddy and granny, like ud never believe. so she was mad when i wanted to go visit them. and of course when i got there my granny was mad becuz i forgot to remind my dad of somethin so she yelled at me. i wish my dad would take his balls from the jar that my mom obviously carries with her, and get me out of this house. i cant do it without some backin from him. i am strong, but not that strong. i have a heart that my mom can manipulate so well.i have lost all my respect for my dad becuz he cant face my mom even if its for my own good.
the elections, what can i say, i was ready to do the job, i really wanted it, and i am really upset about this whole ordeal. my whole life i have been second best at everything. truely. no matter how hard i try i am always second. in softball we had a perfect season year b4 last until the last game, it was the only other undefeated team that we played, and i lost the game for us. it has always happened like that.
i have soo much homework its not even cool. the papers just keep pourin into my brain like rain in a puddle.i think i have too many classes.
my weekend just keeps cheerin me up. i saw a good movie, went to the beach, went flounderin, went to the art show, ate flounder wit moo moo and the rest of the family, swam at vrotex and actually enjoyed the car ride wit vince and mark (somewhat), saw fireworks, went on a pontoon boat wit ali to crab island, and watched miami LOOSE to fsu 10-7.
i kw this is completely narsistic but i had to get this off my chest.

Football Saturday!!! my mom has went to work at a shelter in defuniak, and our houseguests are doin laundry, so i get to watch nething i want today, and no one can complain.

last nite was completely awesome. ive got a lot to think about, mor eto complain about, but i dont wanna make neone listen to my ramblin today. no more chilis, next time we're goin to sonic or somethin, i dont care, im sick of chilis. the movie was o cool. i loved when she kicked him and the shoe stuck in his leg, that was awesome. the beach was beautiful, i wish id had a b/f to walk down the beach wit me. but, the talk wit erica was an excellent substitute.

i feel like crap. this cold sux, its just a snotty nose, so maybe ive started gettin allergies for the first time, or i really am suffering from nastinoseidis. i dunno, i hate to admit im sick cuz then i feel helpless and dependent. well, half time is over so im gonna go finish watchin the game, and do some homework. ttfn!
